# Test: WithAssetEventsSameDay
# Purpose: Tests a same-day buy+sell combined with capital returns and accumulation
#          dividends adjusting the Section 104 cost base
# Rules Tested: Same Day Rule (TCGA92/S105(1)), Section 104 Pooling, Capital Returns
#               (CAPRETURN), Accumulation dividends (ACCUMULATION)
# Complexity: High
# Key Features: Same-day buy AND sell, two corporate-action pairs, the later pair
#               adjusts only the shares still held after the disposal
# Expected Outcome: 2019/20 net gain £200.31 (Same-Day leg -£8.25 + Section 104 leg £208.56)
#
# Verification Status: Verified
# Verified By: Reconciled against golden output 2026-06-21
# Verification Notes: Matches tests/json/WithAssetEventsSameDay.json and
#                     tests/plain/WithAssetEventsSameDay.txt. See detailed verification below.
#
# === SECTION 104 POOL (pre-sale) ===
#
#   Buy 1: 2018-08-29, 20 @ £184.65 + £12.50 fees = £3,705.50
#   Buy 2: 2019-03-15, 20 @ £181.56 + £2.00 fees  = £3,633.20
#   Pool: 40 shares, £7,338.70  (avg £183.4675/share)
#   2019-05-31 CAPRETURN 40, £149.75 (reduces pool cost):   £7,338.70 - £149.75 = £7,188.95
#   2019-05-31 ACCUMULATION 40, £150.24 (raises pool cost): £7,188.95 + £150.24 = £7,339.19
#   Pool: 40 shares, £7,339.19  (avg £183.47975/share)
#
# === DISPOSAL: 2019-11-05 SELL 40 shares ===
#
# The 2019-11-05 BUY 20 is a same-day acquisition; it is matched to the sale and
# never enters the Section 104 pool.
# Gross proceeds: 40 × £194.22 = £7,768.80
# Net proceeds:   £7,768.80 - £12.50 fees = £7,756.30
# Each 20-share leg's net proceeds: 20 × £194.22 - (£12.50 × 20/40)
#                                 = £3,884.40 - £6.25 = £3,878.15
#
# Matching order (CG51560): Same Day -> Bed & Breakfast -> Section 104
#   Same Day:    20 shares matched to the 2019-11-05 buy
#   Section 104: remaining 20 shares from the pool
#
# Same-Day leg (20 shares):
#   Allowable cost = 20 × £194.22 + £2.00 = £3,886.40
#   Loss = £3,878.15 - £3,886.40 = -£8.25
#
# Section 104 leg (20 shares):
#   Unit cost = £7,339.19 / 40 = £183.47975/share
#   Allowable cost = 20 × £183.47975 = £3,669.595  ->  £3,669.60
#   Gain = £3,878.15 - £3,669.595 = £208.555  ->  £208.56
#   Pool drained: 40 - 20 = 20 shares; £7,339.19 - £3,669.595 = £3,669.595
#
# === SECTION 104 POOL (post-sale) ===
#
# The later corporate actions adjust only the 20 shares still held. The same-day
# and Section 104 shares disposed on 2019-11-05 have already left the pool
# (CG51560; TCGA92/S110(8)(d)), so they take no part of these returns.
#   2019-11-30 CAPRETURN 20, £95.12:     £3,669.595 - £95.12 = £3,574.475
#   2019-11-30 ACCUMULATION 20, £110.93: £3,574.475 + £110.93 = £3,685.405  ->  £3,685.41
#   Pool: 20 shares, £3,685.41  (avg £184.27/share)
#
# === FINAL RESULT (2019/20) ===
#   Disposals: 1
#   Gross proceeds: £7,768.80
#   Net proceeds: £7,756.30
#   Total allowable cost: £3,886.40 + £3,669.60 = £7,556.00
#   Net gain: £208.56 - £8.25 = £200.31  (golden total_gain £200.31, total_loss £0)
#   Annual exemption: £12,000.00  ->  Taxable gain: £0.00
#   Final holding: 20 shares, £3,685.41 (avg £184.27/share)
